ğŸ“Œ Overview

XDR-Tester is a production-safe security audit tool designed to evaluate the effectiveness of XDR / EDR solutions on Windows endpoints.

The project focuses on controlled adversary emulation, generating real behavioral telemetry without exploiting vulnerabilities or causing system damage.
Its primary goal is to answer a simple but critical question:

Does our endpoint protection actually detect and block real attack behaviors?

ğŸ¯ Design Goals

Safe for production environments

Behavior-based testing (not signatures)

No data destruction, no credential dumping

Clear distinction between blocked vs allowed actions

Actionable reporting for Blue / Purple / Security Engineering teams

ğŸ§  Core Concepts

Simulates real attack techniques, not malware

Uses WinAPI through hardened C# bindings

Differentiates between:

ALERT â†’ attack succeeded (security risk)

BLOCK / FAIL â†’ protection worked as expected

Generates HTML audit reports for non-technical stakeholders

ğŸ§© Implemented Techniques (MITRE ATT&CK Oriented)
Technique	Description
Ransomware behavior	AES-256 memory encryption + VSS interaction
Credential Access	LSASS OpenProcess probing (no dump)
Persistence	Registry Run key modification
Command & Control	HTTPS beaconing (/favicon.ico)
Process Injection (safe)	Handle enumeration + global keyboard hook
Keylogging (audit-safe)	Global hook with CallNextHookEx (no capture)

All techniques are implemented in a non-destructive, reversible, and auditable manner.

ğŸ›¡ï¸ Security & Stability

Garbage Collector safe (global delegate references)

Correct WinAPI contracts (no undefined behavior)

No UI freezing (WPF dispatcher control)

Context-aware execution (Admin vs User mode)

Full cleanup after every test

The tool is explicitly designed not to bypass security, but to test if security reacts properly.

